A quick ruby script to grab the texts from the backups on your computer and print them in a PDF

Warning: This script will only work on OSX and has not been tested extensively. Tested On Mac OSX, Ruby 1.9.2

Requirements: Ruby, RubyGems, sqlite3-ruby, prawn

If you don't have RubyGems: Go here (http://rubygems.org/pages/download) and follow the steps. Start by downloading the zip.

Install Gems:
gem install sqlite3-ruby
gem install prawn

	Note: You may be required to put sudo before each gem install command

How To Use:
./relation-text.rb {phone number}

Enter the digits of the phone number that you want to grab the texts of and a PDF will be created in the same directory